01:06:47.088 --> 01:06:48.419
No. you just limit
your choices.

958
01:06:48.523 --> 01:06:50.013
Seriously.
you need to stop.

959
01:06:50.091 --> 01:06:51.854
You really need
to stop shoving

960
01:06:51.926 --> 01:06:55.885
your psychotic idea of '50s
womanhood down my throat.

961
01:06:58.900 --> 01:07:02.358
And pageants? I mean. what
have they ever done for you?

962
01:07:02.670 --> 01:07:05.400
That's my point. Bliss!

963
01:07:05.506 --> 01:07:06.768
I didn't have a mother..

964
01:07:06.874 --> 01:07:10.275
- ..to navigate all my opportunities.
- Jesus Christ.

965
01:07:10.378 --> 01:07:13.211
I am in love with this.

966
01:07:15.083 --> 01:07:17.176
I mean.
don't you get it?

967
01:07:17.251 --> 01:07:18.775
It won't last.

968
01:07:19.287 --> 01:07:22.848
In two or three years. it'll
be over. This is a moment.

969
01:07:22.924 --> 01:07:24.892
Well. how great is that?

970
01:07:26.561 --> 01:07:28.358
You don't understand.

971
01:07:28.429 --> 01:07:30.693
You will when you have
to support yourself.

972
01:07:30.765 --> 01:07:32.027
I do support myself.

973
01:07:32.100 --> 01:07:33.590
No. you don't.

974
01:07:33.701 --> 01:07:35.464
You buy shoes.

975
01:07:43.311 --> 01:07:45.472
You're full of shit.

976
01:07:46.547 --> 01:07:47.912
You know what.
actually...

977
01:07:47.982 --> 01:07:49.074
Hey.

978
01:07:49.150 --> 01:07:50.913
Hey. you calm down.
little lady.

979
01:07:50.985 --> 01:07:53.419
Why don't you go back
to your turtle shell

980
01:07:53.488 --> 01:07:56.582
so you don't have to
freaking confront anything?

981
01:08:09.670 --> 01:08:11.160
You all right?

982
01:08:15.009 --> 01:08:16.806
I just don't
wanna talk about it.

983
01:08:16.911 --> 01:08:18.902
Pash. come on.

984
01:08:19.847 --> 01:08:21.974
You told me
to wait for you.

985
01:08:22.083 --> 01:08:24.278
I was so busy waiting for you
that I didn't notice the cop

986
01:08:24.352 --> 01:08:26.343
coming over to arrest me
for an open container.

987
01:08:26.454 --> 01:08:27.944
Shit. are you okay?

988
01:08:28.022 --> 01:08:30.149
No. actually I'm
not okay. all right?

989
01:08:30.525 --> 01:08:34.791
On top of everything. my parents
decided to put a GPS in my car

990
01:08:34.862 --> 01:08:37.524
so they can track
my every goddamn move.

991
01:08:40.535 --> 01:08:42.503
So what's your problem?

992
01:08:42.603 --> 01:08:45.128
Hope the joyride with your
boyfriend was worth it.

993
01:08:45.206 --> 01:08:48.266
Wait. wait.
How is this my fault. okay?

994
01:08:48.342 --> 01:08:49.639
I didn't put that
drink in your hand.

995
01:08:49.710 --> 01:08:52.543
You know what? I'm ecstatic
that you have this whole new life

996
01:08:52.647 --> 01:08:54.478
and you have all new
friends and it's great.

997
01:08:54.549 --> 01:08:58.645
But I'm trying to get out of this
armpit of a town just as much as you.

998
01:08:58.719 --> 01:09:00.880
And last time I checked.

999
01:09:00.988 --> 01:09:03.980
getting arrested is not
the kind of extracurricular

1000
01:09:04.058 --> 01:09:06.788
that Ivy League schools
are looking for.

1001
01:09:07.495 --> 01:09:12.159
Do you really think that this roller
derby career of yours is going anywhere?

1002
01:09:13.467 --> 01:09:14.491
That's not what
it's about.

1003
01:09:14.569 --> 01:09:16.230
Oh. yeah. right.

1004
01:09:16.337 --> 01:09:17.895
I'm sorry. Pash.

1005
01:09:26.881 --> 01:09:28.712
Thanks for
letting me stay.

1006
01:09:28.816 --> 01:09:29.908
Anytime.

1007
01:09:32.753 --> 01:09:35.847
That's Riley back there.
He's my little man.

1008
01:09:38.860 --> 01:09:41.055
So that's why you never
come out with us?

1009
01:09:41.162 --> 01:09:43.858
Yeah. he pretty much owns
my ass. Don't you. Rile?

1010
01:09:46.000 --> 01:09:49.436
Okay. first stop. sitter.
Then the Warehouse.

1011
01:10:00.114 --> 01:10:03.379
Ruthless. Ruthless.
Ruthless.

1012
01:10:05.286 --> 01:10:07.083
Maven. Maven. Maven?

1013
01:10:08.856 --> 01:10:10.790
Hey. guess how old I am.

1014
01:10:12.860 --> 01:10:14.054
Twenty-seven?

1015
01:10:14.128 --> 01:10:15.459
Oh. that's sweet.

1016
01:10:17.131 --> 01:10:19.429
I'm 36

1017
01:10:21.369 --> 01:10:23.564
Guess when I
started skating.

1018
01:10:24.205 --> 01:10:25.638
I was 31.

1019
01:10:26.741 --> 01:10:32.907
'Cause it took me that long to find
one thing that I was really good at.

1020
01:10:36.284 --> 01:10:40.744
And you know what? I
worked my ass off to get it.

1021
01:10:42.924 --> 01:10:44.391
Yeah. me. too.

1022
01:10:45.793 --> 01:10:47.988
It's too bad
you're only 17.

1023
01:10:50.131 --> 01:10:53.760
What do you think the league is
gonna say when they find that out?

1024
01:10:53.834 --> 01:10:57.600
Or your teammates. when they
find out you've been lying?

1025
01:10:57.672 --> 01:11:00.004
That's gonna be rough.
Maven. please. Look...

1026
01:11:00.107 --> 01:11:01.574
No. you look.

1027
01:11:01.642 --> 01:11:05.134
One day it will be your time.
Ruthless. but it's not your time now.

1028
01:11:05.246 --> 01:11:09.182
And if I was you. I wouldn't even
bother lacing up those skates.

1029
01:11:30.204 --> 01:11:31.296
Fuck.

1030
01:11:33.841 --> 01:11:36.639
<i>It's Oliver. I'm running
with the bulls right now.</i>

1031
01:11:37.845 --> 01:11:39.210
Hey. Oliver.

1032
01:11:41.382 --> 01:11:45.375
I just need to talk to you. I...
I'm calling you from a payphone.

1033
01:11:48.489 --> 01:11:50.286
Look. I've left home.

1034
01:11:53.828 --> 01:11:57.821
I... You know. this...
I don't...

1035
01:11:57.898 --> 01:12:00.196
I don't wanna do this
on voicemail.

1036
01:12:00.301 --> 01:12:03.998
so maybe you can get me
on Maggie's phone.

1037
01:12:05.072 --> 01:12:09.031
512-697-4998

1038
01:12:10.511 --> 01:12:14.572
And then we can just... We
can talk later. Okay. bye.

1039
01:12:18.486 --> 01:12:20.181
- Oink Joint
- Hey. B.

1040
01:12:20.588 --> 01:12:21.748
Hey. Bliss.

1041
01:12:21.856 --> 01:12:23.016
<i>Is Pash there?</i>

1042
01:12:25.326 --> 01:12:26.850
She's not here.

1043
01:12:31.098 --> 01:12:32.690
Yeah. okay.
Bye.

1044
01:12:44.512 --> 01:12:49.677
If. you know. you hear a
hint of pain in my voice

1045
01:12:49.750 --> 01:12:52.446
when I say that I've
lost my best friend..

1046
01:12:52.553 --> 01:12:56.011
..to a gang of
roller skating she-males

1047
01:12:56.624 --> 01:12:59.889
and that the only highlight of my
night was serving corn to an old man

1048
01:12:59.960 --> 01:13:03.896
who can't even chew it.
then I'd say you're wrong.

1049
01:13:06.700 --> 01:13:08.031
I'm happy.

1050
01:13:24.418 --> 01:13:27.717
Okay. that was odd.

1051
01:13:32.226 --> 01:13:33.750
Oddly glorious.

1052
01:13:35.429 --> 01:13:37.294
Ruthless. what's up?

1053
01:13:38.933 --> 01:13:42.164
I just had something
I wanted to tell you all.

1054
01:13:42.603 --> 01:13:44.468
Seventeen!?

1055
01:13:44.572 --> 01:13:45.766
What if you'd
gotten hurt?

1056
01:13:45.840 --> 01:13:47.933
Her parents could sue
the league. you guys.

1057
01:13:48.008 --> 01:13:48.997
I know.

1058
01:13:49.110 --> 01:13:50.975
We're in enough trouble with
the fire marshal as it is.

1059
01:13:51.112 --> 01:13:52.739
- Exactly.
- You know what? She can still play..

1060
01:13:52.847 --> 01:13:56.305
..as long as she gets permission
from one of her parents.

1061
01:13:58.452 --> 01:13:59.680
I can't.

1062
01:13:59.954 --> 01:14:03.117
I'm not even living
at home right now.

1063
01:14:03.190 --> 01:14:07.650
Well. even though you can't skate
with us. and you're a big liar.

1064
01:14:07.761 --> 01:14:09.786
You're still
a Hurl Scout.

1065
01:14:09.997 --> 01:14:12.192
Yeah. you could
be our mascot.

1066
01:14:17.771 --> 01:14:21.502
You can't understand until you
have one. everything changes.

1067
01:14:23.711 --> 01:14:26.305
Yeah. that's what
my mom always says.

1068
01:14:26.714 --> 01:14:28.545
But you're not
really like her. though.

1069
01:14:28.682 --> 01:14:29.979
Oh. I'm the cool aunt?

1070
01:14:30.050 --> 01:14:31.176
Yeah.

1071
01:14:34.722 --> 01:14:38.522
Why don't I just cut school and
hang out with you guys today?

1072
01:14:39.860 --> 01:14:41.521
Bliss. I know what it's like
to wanna do your own thing.

1073
01:14:41.629 --> 01:14:42.721
believe me. I do.

1074
01:14:42.830 --> 01:14:45.458
But maybe there's
a way you can do it

1075
01:14:45.533 --> 01:14:48.366
without making your
parents feel like crap?

1076
01:14:49.403 --> 01:14:51.337
What?
I've just been thinking.

1077
01:14:51.405 --> 01:14:55.068
I think maybe you're being a
little selfish with your mom.

1078
01:14:59.914 --> 01:15:01.245
Okay. no.

1079
01:15:02.917 --> 01:15:05.681
She's the one who has
been shoving her agenda

1080
01:15:05.753 --> 01:15:07.983
down my throat
since day one.

1081
01:15:09.156 --> 01:15:12.648
First of all. you're lucky
to have a mom that even cares.

1082
01:15:12.726 --> 01:15:14.523
And just because
she's wrong about derby.

1083
01:15:14.595 --> 01:15:17.894
doesn't mean she's wrong
about every single thing.

1084
01:15:17.998 --> 01:15:21.195
And if Riley ever lies to me
the way you lied to your parents.

1085
01:15:21.268 --> 01:15:23.736
He wouldn't even be able to run
away 'cause I'd break his legs.

1086
01:15:25.105 --> 01:15:27.835
I'm just kidding. honey.
That was a joke.

1087
01:15:30.578 --> 01:15:32.045
I am here for you.

1088
01:15:32.112 --> 01:15:37.106
but just because you've found a new family
doesn't mean you throw the old one away.

1089
01:15:48.629 --> 01:15:51.291
Have a swell day at
school. sweetheart.

1090
01:15:53.801 --> 01:15:55.098
You didn't see that.
did you?

1091
01:17:14.214 --> 01:17:16.546
Please don't
judge me right now.

1092
01:17:23.457 --> 01:17:28.292
Whoever he is.
He doesn't deserve you.

1093
01:17:30.898 --> 01:17:32.229
Come here.

1094
01:17:36.904 --> 01:17:38.303
I feel sick.

1095
01:17:39.673 --> 01:17:41.163
I know you do.

1096
01:17:51.418 --> 01:17:53.318
I gave him everything.

1097
01:17:53.854 --> 01:17:56.755
No. don't say that.

1098
01:18:05.599 --> 01:18:07.089
No. it's true.

1099
01:18:09.770 --> 01:18:10.930
I did.

1100
01:18:40.300 --> 01:18:42.291
That's a lot to process.

1101
01:18:48.642 --> 01:18:51.133
She was wearing
my Stryper T-shirt.

1102
01:18:52.079 --> 01:18:54.309
I just don't understand
how he could do that.

1103
01:18:54.415 --> 01:18:55.882
Your T-shirt?

1104
01:18:57.718 --> 01:19:00.118
It's the only
cool thing you own.

1105
01:19:00.387 --> 01:19:01.979
That you'd know about.

1106
01:19:03.290 --> 01:19:04.655
Stryper.

1107
01:19:10.597 --> 01:19:12.792
Mom. this isn't...

1108
01:19:13.600 --> 01:19:16.068
This isn't working.

1109
01:19:17.938 --> 01:19:19.132
I know.

1110
01:19:20.307 --> 01:19:22.639
You just make me
feel so guilty.

1111
01:19:24.011 --> 01:19:27.572
That's not what I want.

1112
01:19:29.583 --> 01:19:31.483
I deserve it sometimes.

1113
01:19:32.019 --> 01:19:38.117
Well. I know I can go
overboard sometimes.

1114
01:19:40.093 --> 01:19:43.585
But when the person that
you love more than anything

1115
01:19:43.664 --> 01:19:46.531
tells you
that you suck. it...

1116
01:19:49.470 --> 01:19:53.133
If you want me to do the Miss
Blue Bonnet pageant. I will.

1117
01:19:53.207 --> 01:19:56.267
No. no. no. no.
We're way past that.

1118
01:19:56.343 --> 01:19:59.972
No. it's not a big deal. I
mean. we already got the dress.

1119
01:20:04.885 --> 01:20:07.149
Don't do it for me.

1120
01:20:08.355 --> 01:20:10.516
Fine. I'll do it
for myself.

1121
01:20:17.998 --> 01:20:19.829
Look who's back.

1122
01:20:20.834 --> 01:20:21.892
Hi.

1123
01:20:29.409 --> 01:20:31.036
Glad you're safe.

1124
01:20:33.514 --> 01:20:35.744
I shouldn't have said
those things to you.

1125
01:20:40.220 --> 01:20:42.245
Already forgotten. kiddo.

1126
01:20:52.199 --> 01:20:54.997
<i>She's trying to
look pathetic on purpose.</i>

1127
01:20:59.172 --> 01:21:01.936
How long you gonna
hold onto that grudge?

1128
01:21:12.286 --> 01:21:13.514
Thanks.

1129
01:21:16.757 --> 01:21:19.282
Pash. I'm sorry.
You see. I just...

1130
01:21:19.393 --> 01:21:20.883
Come on.

1131
01:21:20.961 --> 01:21:22.292
I'm sorry.

1132
01:21:25.299 --> 01:21:26.960
I'm really sorry.

1133
01:21:28.135 --> 01:21:29.363
I know.

1134
01:21:31.238 --> 01:21:33.638
Just keep...
Keep saying it.

1135
01:21:33.740 --> 01:21:34.764
Yeah.

1136
01:21:34.875 --> 01:21:36.240
Over and over
again. please.

1137
01:21:36.310 --> 01:21:38.471
Yeah. I will.
I'll keep it up.

1138
01:21:40.314 --> 01:21:41.440
So what happened?

1139
01:21:41.548 --> 01:21:44.984
God. I just feel
like such...

1140
01:21:45.485 --> 01:21:50.718
I'm stupid. I'm just... I feel
so stupid for falling for it.

1141
01:21:51.592 --> 01:21:54.584
Yeah. that's why I like
a good fondling. you know?

1142
01:21:54.661 --> 01:21:56.458
It's so much simpler.

1143
01:21:57.564 --> 01:22:02.331
Well. while you were
off gallivanting. I...

1144
01:22:03.837 --> 01:22:05.498
I got some news.

1145
01:22:07.274 --> 01:22:09.071
What... What... What's...

1146
01:22:09.509 --> 01:22:11.500
I got into some colleges.

1147
01:22:13.013 --> 01:22:14.105
Wow!

1148
01:22:14.181 --> 01:22:16.411
My parents want me
to go to Johns Hopkins.

1149
01:22:16.483 --> 01:22:20.817
but I think I'm
gonna go to Columbia.

1150
01:22:20.921 --> 01:22:24.982
I know. I'm gonna see what it's like
to live in New York for a little while.

1151
01:22:25.092 --> 01:22:27.026
That's amazing.

1152
01:22:33.467 --> 01:22:35.958
Do you still have
his stupid jacket?

1153
01:22:45.178 --> 01:22:47.339
Did he turn into
a handsome prince?

1154
01:22:47.447 --> 01:22:49.039
No. he stayed a Birdman.

1155
01:22:49.716 --> 01:22:53.174
But the worst part is.
he's actually a good kisser.

1156
01:22:54.554 --> 01:22:56.112
Really good.

1157
01:22:56.223 --> 01:22:58.316
Congratulations
are in order.

1158
01:22:58.392 --> 01:23:01.122
Uh. no. Let's not
encourage this.

1159
01:23:02.229 --> 01:23:04.356
I like Birdman.
He's nice.

1160
01:23:04.464 --> 01:23:08.161
Hey. Bliss. somebody on the
phone for you. A Maggie Mayhem?

1161
01:23:09.369 --> 01:23:10.393
Well. look at you.

1162
01:23:10.504 --> 01:23:11.493
I got a makeover.

1163
01:23:11.571 --> 01:23:13.061
Yes. you did.

1164
01:23:18.245 --> 01:23:19.405
Hello.

1165
01:23:19.513 --> 01:23:20.844
<i>Ruthless.
it's the championship.</i>

1166
01:23:20.914 --> 01:23:23.314
<i>Don't even tell me
you can't make it.</i>

1167
01:23:23.383 --> 01:23:24.407
<i>I can't.</i>

1168
01:23:25.018 --> 01:23:28.419
Is it her mom? Let me talk
to her. I'll knock her out.

1169
01:23:29.389 --> 01:23:31.254
Just tell your mom
it's important.

1170
01:23:32.225 --> 01:23:34.989
The pageant is the same day
as the game. and I can't.

1171
01:23:35.062 --> 01:23:38.327
<i>Well. you have to try harder and
you have to make it work. We need you.</i>

1172
01:23:38.432 --> 01:23:39.865
<i>- Let me talk to her mom.
- Bye.</i>

1173
01:23:39.933 --> 01:23:41.867
<i>I'll kick her in her...</i>

1174
01:23:43.003 --> 01:23:44.732
You're selling out.

1175
01:24:00.854 --> 01:24:02.446
"Babe Ruthless."

1176
01:24:03.523 --> 01:24:05.718
<i>A classic
move in derby.</i>

1177
01:24:05.792 --> 01:24:08.852
<i>Babe and Maggie go for the
whip. and it's effective.</i>

1178
01:24:08.929 --> 01:24:13.423
<i>Nothing gives you speed like
a whip. Look at Ruthless fly.</i>

1179
01:24:23.076 --> 01:24:24.737
Excuse me. ladies.

1180
01:24:25.378 --> 01:24:28.814
I'm looking for Maggie.
Maggie Mayhem.

1181
01:24:33.653 --> 01:24:35.450
Good pageant. y'all.

1182
01:24:38.992 --> 01:24:40.789
Love the dress. Amber.

1183
01:24:45.065 --> 01:24:47.659
<i>- We'll have to break through.
- I know.</i>

1184
01:24:47.834 --> 01:24:49.165
<i>What time is it?</i>

1185
01:24:51.838 --> 01:24:54.602
- Your gown is custom. huh?
- Yeah.

1186
01:24:54.674 --> 01:24:56.938
It's beautiful.

1187
01:24:57.010 --> 01:24:58.307
Thanks.

1188
01:25:00.180 --> 01:25:02.410
Your dress is nice
too Amber.

1189
01:25:04.518 --> 01:25:05.849
- Hey.
- Hey.

1190
01:25:07.654 --> 01:25:09.246
We need to talk.

1191
01:25:14.761 --> 01:25:16.786
Ma'am. put down
the lip gloss.

1192
01:25:16.863 --> 01:25:18.296
Step away from the mirror.

1193
01:25:20.667 --> 01:25:23.363
What are you all doing
here? Are you...

1194
01:25:23.770 --> 01:25:25.294
You're just springing
this on me now?

1195
01:25:25.372 --> 01:25:26.862
I know the timing sucks.

1196
01:25:26.973 --> 01:25:29.134
but I've been thinking. You
know. I'm not so bothered

1197
01:25:29.209 --> 01:25:31.177
by her playing
this roller derby.

1198
01:25:31.278 --> 01:25:32.768
In fact. I think
it's kind of neat.

1199
01:25:32.846 --> 01:25:35.781
I went on the website. they got
Blisster's pictures all over.

1200
01:25:35.849 --> 01:25:37.646
And it looks like they're
